Example
Find out whether the browser is online:

Copy
let x = "Is the browser online? " + navigator.onLine;

Description
The onLine property returns a Boolean value that tells whether the browser is in online or offline mode.

This property is read-only.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
onLine	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
let a = navigator.onLine;
Return Value
A Boolean, indicating whether the browser is in online or offline mode.

Returns true if the browser is online, otherwise it returns false

